<L>__{exterior parking lot day}
<A>__{exley walks lynn out.}
<C>__{exley}
<D>__{where will you go?}
<C>__{lynn}
<D>__{bisbee, arizona. the air's good for pensioners and i know where everything is.}
<C>__{exley}
<D>__{when?}
<C>__{lynn}
<D>__{right now, before i back down.}
<C>__{exley}
<D>__{where is he?}
<A>__{lynn gestures ahead. they walk to her car. she opens the back door. bud's in the back. braces on his legs, head sutured. jaw wired shut and tubes running in and out. but his hands still look strong. bud forces a smile through the wires, tries to say something, but can't.}
<C>__{exley}
<D>__{thanks for the push.}
<A>__{exley takes his hand. bud squeezes till both men wince.}
<C>__{exley}
<D>__{you just did what you did. no rank, no glory.}
<A>__{exley slips his medal of valor into bud's hand.}
<C>__{exley}
<D>__{from me to you. it'll mean something if it's yours.}
<A>__{bud takes it, turns away so exley won't see the tears.}
<C>__{lynn}
<D>__{we should go now.}
<A>__{as exley steps back, lynn closes the door. party noises drift from upstairs. exley looks to lynn.}
<C>__{exley}
<D>__{do you think i ever could've been in the running?}
<C>__{lynn}
<D>__{some men get the world. others get ex hookers and a trip to arizona.}
<A>__{a beat. exley wishes he'd gotten the trip to arizona. she kisses him on the cheek, gets in the car. starts it. exley looks back at bud. bud presses his hands to the glass. exley touches his side, palms half the man's size. hands against hands. the car moves. a turn into traffic, a good bye toot on the horn. exley's all alone. as he watches them go...}
